Sentencas: U cations were immobilized in the traditional Sr2Fe2O6-delta (SFO) oxide, which was subsequently evaluated as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs).
Titulo: Immobilizing U cations in Sr2Fe2O6-δ as a new cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Experimental studies indicated that the U cations could be incorporated into the SFO lattice, forming the new Sr2Fe1.5U0.5O6-delta (SFUO) oxide material.
Titulo: Immobilizing U cations in Sr2Fe2O6-δ as a new cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SFUO material exhibited improved chemical stability than the SFO material, preventing the formation of carbonates after treatment in a CO2 atmosphere.
Titulo: Immobilizing U cations in Sr2Fe2O6-δ as a new cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Although the total electrical conductivity was decreased with the U-doping, the surface catalytic activity of SFUO was improved compared with SFO, which was demonstrated by first-principles calculations.
Titulo: Immobilizing U cations in Sr2Fe2O6-δ as a new cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The subsequent electrochemical studies indicated that an H-SOFC using the SFUO cathode showed higher fuel cell output and smaller polarization resistance than the SFO cathode.
Titulo: Immobilizing U cations in Sr2Fe2O6-δ as a new cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The present study demonstrated that SFO could locate U cations in the lattice, and the produced SFUO oxide exhibited improved performance, suggesting the utilization of SFO cathode in the harsh environment (such as U-containing conditions) would be possible, and the electrochemical performance of the fuel cell is not reduced.
Titulo: Immobilizing U cations in Sr2Fe2O6-δ as a new cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
